<font color="#FF0000">VISIT TO FORT HOOD, TEXAS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov 20 10:58:54 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Just returned from my inspection tour of the famous Fourth Infantry Division, named after me, Mustang two &quot;FOUR.&quot; I dropped the Commanding General and made him give me fifty for not having a glass of Koolaid on the podium.  Never have I seen so many Full Bulls and Command Sergeant Majors under one roof.<br>
It was a first class event..they even provided a Marine to buff the floor and park cars.. a real joint military effort!(I understand that they requested two Marines..but the Navy refused..claimed that they were having a &quot;Circus&quot; party for deprived kids and needed at least one guy in a clown suit.)<br>
I delivered my speech, co-written by Stephen King and Daniell Steel, with such bravado, that all were impressed.<br>
The Commanding General of III Corps offered me his rank and position if I would stay on and inspire his troops.  I made him drop and give me fifty for making such a foolish request in view of the fact that deer season (rifle) begins Saturday!<br><br>
Something that may grab you by the stacking swivel.. their most consistant and emphatic request, when I left..was to tell you guys how much they respect and appreciate you.<br><br>
You are revered and held in high esteem by all the men and women of the Fourth Infantry Division.<br><br>
I took all of you, in spirit, with me.  You made a motley formation in the center of my heart, lifting up this &quot;Old Warrior's&quot; battered head.<br><br>
Thanks Bros
<p><code>-- Those tears aren't from crying.....  (Cookie's standing downwind!) </code><p>


